🧾 3. SERVICE MIGRATION CHECKLIST (USE FOR ALL 15 SERVICES)

✅ Pre-Migration
	•	Service dependencies mapped (DB, MQ, APIs)
	•	Data model validated
	•	Idempotency check (important for MQ)
	•	Observability enabled
	•	Rollback plan defined

⸻

✅ Shadow Deployment
	•	Deploy service in AWS via Argo CD
	•	Connect to ON-PREM DB + MQ
	•	No external traffic

⸻

✅ Data Sync
	•	PostgreSQL replication active
	•	RabbitMQ federation active
	•	Lag monitoring enabled

⸻

✅ Parallel Run
	•	AWS service processing messages
	•	Outputs compared (reconciliation)
	•	No mismatches

⸻

✅ Cutover
	•	Freeze producers
	•	Drain queues
	•	Final DB sync
	•	Switch:
	•	DB → Amazon RDS for PostgreSQL
	•	MQ → Amazon MQ

⸻

✅ Post-Cutover
	•	Monitor errors
	•	Validate transactions
	•	Keep rollback ready

⸻

🔁 4. DR + FAILOVER STRATEGY (MANDATORY FOR FINANCE)

⸻

🧠 Multi-Layer DR

Layer 1: Kubernetes
	•	Multi-AZ nodes in Amazon EKS

⸻

Layer 2: Database
	•	Multi-AZ RDS
	•	Read replica (cross-region optional)

⸻

Layer 3: RabbitMQ
	•	Active-standby in Amazon MQ

⸻

Layer 4: Backup
	•	DB snapshots (daily)
	•	S3 backup for configs
	•	Velero for K8s backup

⸻

🔄 Failover Flow

Primary (AWS) fails
   ↓
Promote RDS replica
   ↓
Switch DNS
   ↓
Restart services


⸻

🔙 Rollback (during migration)

AWS issue detected
   ↓
Switch DNS → ON-PREM
   ↓
Resume ON-PREM MQ + DB


⸻

🐇 5. RABBITMQ HA + FAILOVER DESIGN

⸻

During Migration
	•	Federation ON-PREM → AWS

⸻

After Migration

Option A (Recommended)
	•	Fully managed → Amazon MQ

⸻

Message Safety

Ensure:
	•	Publisher confirms enabled
	•	Consumer ACKs enabled
	•	Idempotent consumers

⸻

Anti-Duplication Pattern

if message_id in processed_table:
    skip()
else:
    process()


⸻

🐘 6. POSTGRES PRODUCTION SETUP

⸻

Final Setup
	•	Amazon RDS for PostgreSQL Multi-AZ
	•	Read replica for reporting
	•	Automated backups

⸻

Cutover SQL

SELECT pg_switch_wal();
-- ensure replication caught up


⸻

🧪 7. VALIDATION SYSTEM (CRITICAL)

⸻

What to compare:
	•	DB records
	•	MQ events
	•	API responses

⸻

Example

assert sum(onprem_txn) == sum(aws_txn)
assert count(messages_onprem) == count(messages_aws)


